headline: Lower Mortgage Rates Were Fun While They Lasted. It’s Over for Now.
summary: Tuesday’s bond-market upheaval sent the cost of a 30-year mortgage 0.14 percentage point higher, according to one daily survey.

headline: Higher Treasury Yields Weigh on Home Builder Stocks
summary: A higher 10-year Treasury yield means higher mortgage rates.  The iShares U.S. Home Construction ETF was 1.5% lower in mid-morning trading, on pace for its largest percentage decline since Jan. 7, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  Builder stocks had been riding a wave of optimism spurred by a decline in mortgage rates earlier this month.

headline: D.R. Horton's Q1 Earnings & Revenues Beat, Net Sales Orders Up Y/Y
summary: DHI beats first-quarter fiscal 2026 estimates, but falling margins and affordability pressures keep the housing outlook cautious.
